### ============ DEPLOYED VERSION TESTING ==============
### Test the email password reset flow on deployed Render backend
### 
### Base URL: https://healthcare-connect-dwg6.onrender.com
### Test User: welcometest9@example.com
### Test Password: TestPass123!

@deployedUrl = https://healthcare-connect-dwg6.onrender.com
@testEmail = welcometest9@example.com
@testPassword = TestPass123!

### ============ STEP 1: HEALTH CHECK ==============
### Verify backend is running
GET {{deployedUrl}}/auth/health

###
GET {{deployedUrl}}/health

### ============ STEP 2: TEST EMAIL/SMTP CONNECTION ==============
### This endpoint will test if SMTP is configured and working correctly
### Check the response for any SMTP connection errors
GET {{deployedUrl}}/auth/test-email

### ============ STEP 3: LOGIN TEST ==============
### Test if user exists by attempting login
# @name login_test
POST {{deployedUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{testEmail}}",
  "password": "{{testPassword}}"
}

### ============ STEP 4: FORGOT PASSWORD ==============
### Request password reset email - MAIN TEST
### This should:
### 1. Check if user exists
### 2. Generate OTP
### 3. Store OTP in database
### 4. Send password reset email
### If this fails, check the test-email endpoint output above
# @name forgot_password_test
POST {{deployedUrl}}/auth/forgot-password
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{testEmail}}"
}

### ============ TROUBLESHOOTING ==============
### If forgot-password fails:
### 1. Run test-email endpoint first to check SMTP
### 2. Check backend logs in Render dashboard
### 3. Verify MAIL_HOST, MAIL_USER, MAIL_PASSWORD in .env
### 4. Check if FRONTEND_URL is set correctly
### 5. Look for SMTP connection errors
### 6. Verify templates folder is in dist/mail/templates on Render

### Test with different email
POST {{deployedUrl}}/auth/forgot-password
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "timothykhalayi96@gmail.com"
}

### ============ STEP 5: RESET PASSWORD ==============
### After receiving OTP from email, use it here
### Get OTP code from the email and replace 000000
POST {{deployedUrl}}/auth/reset-password
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{testEmail}}",
  "otp": "000000",
  "newPassword": "NewPassword789!"
}
